[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6886,
        "end_time": 12960,
        "text": "Denis Diderot left a dungeon\noutside Paris on November 3, 1749."
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 12960,
        "end_time": 15412,
        "text": "He&#39;d had his writing \nburned in public before,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 15412,
        "end_time": 18758,
        "text": "but this time, he&#39;d gotten locked up\nunder royal order"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 18758,
        "end_time": 24007,
        "text": "for an essay about a philosopher&#39;s\ndeath bed rejection of God."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 24007,
        "end_time": 28547,
        "text": "To free himself, Denis promised\nnever to write things like that again."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 28547,
        "end_time": 31442,
        "text": "So he got back to work \non something a little like that,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 31442,
        "end_time": 32829,
        "text": "only way worse,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 32829,
        "end_time": 34821,
        "text": "and much bigger."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 34821,
        "end_time": 38941,
        "text": "In 1745, publisher Andr\u00e9 le Breton\nhad hired Diderot"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 38941,
        "end_time": 41803,
        "text": "to adapt the English cyclopedia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 41803,
        "end_time": 45631,
        "text": "or a universal dictionary \nof arts and sciences"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 45631,
        "end_time": 47378,
        "text": "for French subscribers."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 47378,
        "end_time": 50141,
        "text": "A broke writer, Diderot survived\nby translating,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 50141,
        "end_time": 51078,
        "text": "tutoring,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 51078,
        "end_time": 53200,
        "text": "and authoring sermons for priests,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 53200,
        "end_time": 55229,
        "text": "and a pornographic novel once."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 55229,
        "end_time": 58800,
        "text": "Le Breton paired him with co-editor\nJean le Rond d&#39;Alembert,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 58800,
        "end_time": 62597,
        "text": "a math genius found \non a church doorstep as a baby."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 62597,
        "end_time": 65491,
        "text": "Technical dictionaries, \nlike the cyclopedia, weren&#39;t new,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 65491,
        "end_time": 69707,
        "text": "but no one had attempted one publication\ncovering all knowledge,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 69707,
        "end_time": 71133,
        "text": "so they did."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 71133,
        "end_time": 74667,
        "text": "The two men organized \nthe French Enlightenment&#39;s brightest stars"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 74667,
        "end_time": 77818,
        "text": "to produce the first encyclopedia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 77818,
        "end_time": 82585,
        "text": "or rational dictionary of the arts,\nsciences, and crafts."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 82585,
        "end_time": 87609,
        "text": "Assembling every essential fact\nand principle in, as it turned out,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 87609,
        "end_time": 90539,
        "text": "over 70,000 entries,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 90539,
        "end_time": 92429,
        "text": "20,000,000 words"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 92429,
        "end_time": 96200,
        "text": "in 35 volumes of text and illustrations"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 96200,
        "end_time": 99390,
        "text": "created over three decades\nof researching,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 99390,
        "end_time": 100548,
        "text": "writing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 100548,
        "end_time": 101477,
        "text": "arguging,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 101477,
        "end_time": 102443,
        "text": "smuggling,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 102443,
        "end_time": 103565,
        "text": "backstabbing,"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 103565,
        "end_time": 104698,
        "text": "law-breaking,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 104698,
        "end_time": 106761,
        "text": "and alphabetizing."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 106761,
        "end_time": 108627,
        "text": "To organize the work,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 108627,
        "end_time": 112094,
        "text": "Diderot adapted Francis Bacon&#39;s\n&quot;Classification of Knowledge&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 112094,
        "end_time": 116958,
        "text": "into a three-part system based \non the mind&#39;s approaches to reality:"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 116958,
        "end_time": 117710,
        "text": "memory,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 117710,
        "end_time": 118660,
        "text": "reason,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 118660,
        "end_time": 120244,
        "text": "and imagination."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 120244,
        "end_time": 122955,
        "text": "He also emphasized the importance\nof commerce,"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 122955,
        "end_time": 123889,
        "text": "technology,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 123889,
        "end_time": 125300,
        "text": "and crafts,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 125300,
        "end_time": 130582,
        "text": "poking around shops to study the tools\nand techniques of Parisian laborers."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 130582,
        "end_time": 134474,
        "text": "To spotlight a few of the nearly\n150 philosoph contributers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 134474,
        "end_time": 137150,
        "text": "Jean Jacques Rousseau,\nDiderot&#39;s close friend,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 137150,
        "end_time": 140521,
        "text": "wrote much of the music section \nin three months,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 140521,
        "end_time": 143171,
        "text": "and was never reimbursed for copy fees."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 143171,
        "end_time": 147126,
        "text": "His entry on political economy holds ideas\nhe&#39;d later develop further"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 147126,
        "end_time": 149321,
        "text": "in &quot;The Social Contract.&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 149321,
        "end_time": 152506,
        "text": "D&#39;Alembert wrote \nthe famous preliminary discourse,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 152506,
        "end_time": 155142,
        "text": "a key statement \nof the French Enlightenment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 155142,
        "end_time": 157685,
        "text": "championing independent \ninvestigative reasoning"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 157685,
        "end_time": 159809,
        "text": "as the path to progress."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 159809,
        "end_time": 163383,
        "text": "Louis de Jaucourt wrote a quarter\nof the encyclopedia,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 163383,
        "end_time": 165210,
        "text": "18,000 articles,"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 165210,
        "end_time": 166696,
        "text": "5,000,000 words,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 166696,
        "end_time": 168603,
        "text": "unpaid."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 168603,
        "end_time": 171382,
        "text": "Louis once spent 20 years writing a book\non anatomy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 171382,
        "end_time": 173804,
        "text": "shipped it to Amsterdam \nto be published uncensored,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 173804,
        "end_time": 175575,
        "text": "and the ship sank."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 175575,
        "end_time": 177121,
        "text": "Voltaire contributed entries,"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 177121,
        "end_time": 178404,
        "text": "among them history,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 178404,
        "end_time": 179698,
        "text": "elegance,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 179698,
        "end_time": 181469,
        "text": "and fire."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 181469,
        "end_time": 184621,
        "text": "Diderot&#39;s entries sometimes \nexhibit slight bias."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 184621,
        "end_time": 189192,
        "text": "In &quot;political authority,&quot; he dismantled\nthe divine right of kings."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 189192,
        "end_time": 190611,
        "text": "Under &quot;citizen,&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 190611,
        "end_time": 194994,
        "text": "he argued a state was strongest \nwithout great disparity in wealth."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 194994,
        "end_time": 200297,
        "text": "Not surprising from the guy who wrote\npoetry about mankind strangling its kings"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 200297,
        "end_time": 203040,
        "text": "with the entrails of a priest."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 203040,
        "end_time": 207762,
        "text": "So Diderot&#39;s masterpiece wasn&#39;t a hit\nwith the king or highest priest."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 207762,
        "end_time": 209794,
        "text": "Upon release of the first two volumes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 209794,
        "end_time": 214273,
        "text": "Louie XV banned the whole thing\nbut enjoyed his own copy."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 214273,
        "end_time": 217295,
        "text": "Pope Clement XIII ordered it burned."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 217295,
        "end_time": 218643,
        "text": "It was &quot;dangerous,&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 218643,
        "end_time": 220104,
        "text": "&quot;reprehensible,&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 220104,
        "end_time": 222155,
        "text": "as well as &quot;written in French,&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 222155,
        "end_time": 224957,
        "text": "and in &quot;the most seductive style.&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 224957,
        "end_time": 226698,
        "text": "He declared readers excommunicated"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 226698,
        "end_time": 229632,
        "text": "and wanted Diderot arrested on sight."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 229632,
        "end_time": 232303,
        "text": "But Diderot kept a step ahead\nof being shut down,"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 232303,
        "end_time": 235156,
        "text": "smuggling proofs outside France\nfor publication,"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 235156,
        "end_time": 238729,
        "text": "and getting help from allies\nin the French Regime,"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 238729,
        "end_time": 241658,
        "text": "including the King&#39;s mistress,\nMadame de Pompadour,"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 241658,
        "end_time": 245357,
        "text": "and the royal librarian and censor,\nMalesherbes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 245357,
        "end_time": 247839,
        "text": "who tipped Diderot off to impending raids,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 247839,
        "end_time": 251314,
        "text": "and even hid Diderot&#39;s papers\nat his dad&#39;s house."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 251314,
        "end_time": 254310,
        "text": "Still, he faced years of difficulty."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 254310,
        "end_time": 255797,
        "text": "D&#39;Alembert dropped out."
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 255797,
        "end_time": 258623,
        "text": "Rousseau broke off his friendship\nover a line in a play."
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 258623,
        "end_time": 263422,
        "text": "Worse yet, his publisher secretly\nedited some proofs"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 263422,
        "end_time": 265699,
        "text": "to read less radically."
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 265699,
        "end_time": 270015,
        "text": "The uncensored pages reappeared \nin Russia in 1933,"
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 270015,
        "end_time": 272466,
        "text": "long after Diderot had considered\nthe work finished"
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 272466,
        "end_time": 275325,
        "text": "and died at lunch."
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 275325,
        "end_time": 278321,
        "text": "The encyclopedia he left behind\nis many things:"
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 278321,
        "end_time": 280798,
        "text": "a cornerstone of the Enlightenment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 280798,
        "end_time": 283661,
        "text": "a testament \nto France&#39;s crisis of authority,"
    },
    {
        "index": 101,
        "start_time": 283661,
        "end_time": 288043,
        "text": "evidence of popular opinions migration\nfrom pulpit and pew"
    },
    {
        "index": 102,
        "start_time": 288043,
        "end_time": 291161,
        "text": "to cafe, salon, and press."
    },
    {
        "index": 103,
        "start_time": 291161,
        "end_time": 293217,
        "text": "It even has recipes."
    },
    {
        "index": 104,
        "start_time": 293217,
        "end_time": 295476,
        "text": "It&#39;s also irrepressibly human,"
    },
    {
        "index": 105,
        "start_time": 295476,
        "end_time": 300045,
        "text": "as you can tell from Diderot&#39;s entry\nabout a plant named aguaxima."
    },
    {
        "index": 106,
        "start_time": 300045,
        "end_time": 304968,
        "text": "Read it yourself, preferably out loud\nin a French accent."
    }
]